ayers in a multi-cultural neighborhood. &#10;If more non-muslims enroll will they justify ending this practice? Of course not.&#10;And teaching our canadian girls that they are less-than the boys is unacceptable. There is zero comparison to the fact that orthodox jews, for example, sit separately from the women when they pray - firstly it's not about the jews, and the default comparison is weak and pathetic. Second, they pray on private property funded by private funds. Separating the girls from the boys on public school property is obscene. &#10;I think Canadians are simply afraid of reaction. We have lost our way as a society."/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="927" language="en" documentId="1451" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Tdotscribe" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/tempers-flare-over-prayer-in-schools-1.1104775" topic="prayer-in-schools" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="1451" notes="" title="Tempers flare over prayer in schools"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="31"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="32" end="343"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="344" end="425"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="426" end="843"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="55" sofa="1" begin="844" end="927"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51 55"/></xmi:XMI>